00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:59.039
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:05:59.280 --> 00:06:01.710
Let's clear up some common
mistakes people make.

00:06:02.010 --> 00:06:05.729
A big misconception is that
surfacey applies to all loans.

00:06:05.880 --> 00:06:11.700
No, it only applies to secured loans where
an asset is mortgaged or hypothecated, not

00:06:11.700 --> 00:06:14.250
to unsecured loans or agricultural land.

00:06:14.669 --> 00:06:18.870
Another mistake is thinking the act
leaves borrowers with no rights at all.

00:06:19.140 --> 00:06:20.099
That's not true.

00:06:20.340 --> 00:06:23.010
Borrowers have the right
to receive a proper notice.

00:06:23.200 --> 00:06:27.506
They can raise objections and they
can appeal to the DRT and DRAT.

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:31.150
Also, please don't confuse
this with the DRT Act.

00:06:31.419 --> 00:06:33.310
While both deal with debt recovery.

00:06:33.490 --> 00:06:38.289
The DRT ACT requires court intervention
whereas Surfacey allows direct

00:06:38.289 --> 00:06:39.664
action by the secured creditors.

00:06:40.380 --> 00:06:43.770
Banks also cannot just show up
and immediately seize assets.

00:06:44.039 --> 00:06:46.890
They must first issue that 60
day notice to the borrower.

00:06:47.520 --> 00:06:50.669
And finally, remember,
it's not just for banks.

00:06:50.880 --> 00:06:54.390
The act applies to other financial
institutions too, including

00:06:54.390 --> 00:06:57.810
housing finance companies and
asset reconstruction companies.

00:06:58.260 --> 00:06:59.909
WH Framework summary.

00:07:00.419 --> 00:07:02.115
Let's do a quick WH summary.

00:07:02.835 --> 00:07:03.645
What is it?

00:07:04.125 --> 00:07:08.925
The SAR FEI Act 2002, empowering
secured creditors to recover

00:07:08.955 --> 00:07:10.995
NPAs without court intervention.

00:07:11.655 --> 00:07:16.875
Why does it exist to facilitate faster
recovery of bad loans, which improves

00:07:16.875 --> 00:07:21.255
the financial health of institutions
and the stability of the entire sector?

00:07:21.915 --> 00:07:22.995
When is it applied?

00:07:23.500 --> 00:07:27.160
It's applied when a borrower
defaults on a secured loan and the

00:07:27.160 --> 00:07:29.260
account is classified as an NPA.

00:07:29.470 --> 00:07:32.470
But only after a 60 day
notice period has passed.

00:07:33.220 --> 00:07:38.320
Where is it applicable Across India
for secured creditors like banks and

00:07:38.320 --> 00:07:42.760
financial institutions who are trying
to recover dues by enforcing security

00:07:42.760 --> 00:07:44.620
interests over financial assets.

00:07:45.270 --> 00:07:46.320
Who does it involve?

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:50.640
It primarily benefits the secured
creditors by giving them a legal

00:07:50.640 --> 00:07:54.540
framework for direct recovery, and
it impacts defaulting borrowers

00:07:54.690 --> 00:07:58.500
who must settle their dues or face
enforcement action on their assets.

00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:00.180
And how does it work?

00:08:00.630 --> 00:08:05.040
It works by allowing secured creditors
to take possession of secured assets,

00:08:05.130 --> 00:08:09.540
sell them, or even manage the business
all without a court order, but

00:08:09.570 --> 00:08:13.085
only after issuing a formal demand
notice to the defaulting borrower.

